# VALIDATION RULES
# =============================================================================
#
# The env-validator.js script enforces these rules:
#
# PRODUCTION:
# - VITE_API_BASE must use api.ludora.app domain
# - VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID must be ludora-af706
# - VITE_STUDENT_PORTAL_DOMAIN must be my.ludora.app
#
# STAGING:
# - VITE_API_BASE must use staging domain
# - VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID must be ludora-staging
# - VITE_STUDENT_PORTAL_DOMAIN must be my-staging.ludora.app
#
# Run validation: npm run env:check-prod or npm run env:check-staging
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# 1. NEVER commit actual API keys to version control
# 2. Firebase API keys are semi-public (restricted by Firebase security rules)
# 3. Sensitive operations happen server-side with Firebase Admin SDK
# 4. Environment files (.env.*) are gitignored except .env.example
#
# =============================================================================
